China Currently Not Considering a Carbon Tax, NDRC’s Xie Says

-- B y   C h u a   B a i z h e n
-- 
2011-09-22T03:23:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/china-currently-not-considering-a-carbon-tax-ndrc-s-xie-says.html
China  isn’t considering
implementing a carbon tax at the moment,  Xie Zhenhua , vice
chairman of the National Development and Reform Commission, said
at a conference in Beijing today. Establishing a carbon trading
market is the priority, Xie said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
